suppressPackageStartupMessages({

library(tidyverse)
library(janitor)
library(sf)
library(scales)
library(FactoMineR) 
library(factoextra)
})

bevlkerung <- readxl::read_xlsx("data/bevlkerung.xslx")
krankenhuser <- readxl::read_xlsx("data/krankenhuser.xslx") %>% 
  mutate(across(everything(), ~ replace(., is.na(.), 0)))
rztinnen <- readxl::read_xlsx("data/rztinnen.xslx")
bezirke_wien <- readxl::read_xlsx("data/bezirke_wien.xslx")

Resources vs population needs

how are hospital resources allocated proportionally to district population

krankenhuser_auslastung <- krankenhuser %>% 
  filter(Jahr == 2024) %>% 
  group_by(Bezirk_Nr) %>% 
  summarise(
    Systematisierte.Betten = sum(Systematisierte.Betten, na.rm=T),
    rztinnen.und.rzte = sum(rztinnen.und.rzte, na.rm=T),
    Stationre.Patientinnen.und.Patienten = sum(Stationre.Patientinnen.und.Patienten, na.rm=T),
  ) %>% 
  left_join(bevlkerung %>% filter(Jahr == 2024)) %>% 
  print()

model <- krankenhuser_auslastung %>% lm(Systematisierte.Betten ~ Bevlkerung, data=.)
model %>% summary()

krankenhuser_auslastung$residuals <- residuals(model)
krankenhuser_auslastung$anomaly <- ifelse(
  abs(krankenhuser_auslastung$residuals) > sd(krankenhuser_auslastung$residuals)*1.5, 
  "Anomaly", "Normal")

krankenhuser_auslastung %>% 
  # filter(anomaly=="Normal") %>% 
ggplot(aes(x = Bevlkerung, y = Systematisierte.Betten)) +
  geom_point(size = 3, aes(color = anomaly)) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color="gray")+
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Normal" = "steelblue", "Anomaly" = "red")) +
  labs(
    title = "Hospital Beds vs. Population",
    subtitle = "Regression with anomaly detection",
    x = "Population",
    y = "Number of Beds"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

Clustering districts

Hospital capacity

krankenhuser <- krankenhuser %>% 
  mutate(
    patienten_pro_arzt = Stationre.Patientinnen.und.Patienten / rztinnen.und.rzte,
    patienten_pro_bett = Stationre.Patientinnen.und.Patienten / Systematisierte.Betten,
  )

lm_capacity <- krankenhuser %>% lm(Stationre.Patientinnen.und.Patienten ~ Systematisierte.Betten + rztinnen.und.rzte + Personen.in.nicht.rztlichen.Gesundheitsberufen, data = .)
lm_capacity %>% summary()

krankenhuser$residuals <- residuals(lm_capacity)
krankenhuser$efficiency_flag <- ifelse(krankenhuser$residuals > sd(krankenhuser$residuals)*1.5, 
                                        "Overloaded", "Normal")
krankenhuser %>% 
  left_join(bevlkerung) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = rztinnen.und.rzte, 
             y = Stationre.Patientinnen.und.Patienten)) +
  # geom_point(size = 3, aes(color = efficiency_flag)) +
  geom_text(aes(label=Bezirk_Nr, color = efficiency_flag), 
            vjust = 0, hjust = 0, size = 2.5, 
            key_glyph = "point" 
            ) +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", se = FALSE, color="grey") +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Normal" = "steelblue", "Overloaded" = "red")) +
  labs(
    title = "Hospital Workload Regression",
